      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Organizations\" title=\"Organizations\">Organizations</a> * FIDE</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Fidelogo.svg.png/300px-Fidelogo.svg.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"201\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/f/f3/Fidelogo.svg.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Fidelogo.svg.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>FIDE Logo <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p>The <b>Fédération Internationale des Échecs (FIDE)</b> or <b>World Chess Federation</b> is an international organization that acts as the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sport_governing_body\">governing body</a> of international chess competition, organizing the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Chess_Championship\">World Chess Championship</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Women%27s_World_Chess_Championship\">Women's World Chess Championship</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Junior_Chess_Championship\">World Junior and Girls U-20 Chess Championship</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Senior_Chess_Championship\">World Senior Chess Championship</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, \nthe <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Youth_Chess_Championship\">World Youth Chess Championship</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_Olympiad\">Chess Olympiad</a>, the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Team_Chess_Championship\">World Team Chess Championship</a> and regional championships. \nThe FIDE was founded 1924 in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris\">Paris</a> at the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1st_unofficial_Chess_Olympiad\">1st unofficial Chess Olympiad</a> as a kind of players' union by 15 participants and representatives of their countries.   \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Founding_Members\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Founding Members</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#FIDE_Presidents\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">FIDE Presidents</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#FIDE_and_ICGA\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">FIDE and ICGA</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#FIDE_CC_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">FIDE CC Events</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Founding_Members\">Founding Members</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Founding Members\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Istv%C3%A1n_Abonyi\">István Abonyi</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roberto_Grau\">Roberto Grau</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ion_Gudju\">Ion Gudju</a></li>\n<li> Florenziano Marusi</li>\n<li> Marc Nicolet</li>\n<li> Jakov M. Ovadija</li>\n<li> Count Ignacio de Penalver y Zamora</li>\n<li> Major Francis Hooper Rawlins</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Rueb\">Alexander Rueb</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karel_Skali%C4%8Dka\">Karel Skalička</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Francis_Smith\">Stephen Francis Smith</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Izaak_Towbin\">Izaak Towbin</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anatol_Tschepurnoff\">Anatol Tschepurnoff</a></li>\n<li> Pierre Vincent</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newinchess.com/Weltjens__Leon_Willem-ip-88221.html\">Leon Willem Weltjens</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"Presidents\"></span>\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"FIDE_Presidents\">FIDE Presidents</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: FIDE Presidents\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> President\n</th>\n<th> from\n</th>\n<th> until\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Rueb\">Alexander Rueb</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1924\n</td>\n<td>  1949\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Folke_Rogard\">Folke Rogard</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1949\n</td>\n<td>  1970\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Max_Euwe\" title=\"Max Euwe\">Max Euwe</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1970\n</td>\n<td>  1978\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fri%C3%B0rik_%C3%93lafsson\">Friðrik Ólafsson</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1978\n</td>\n<td>  1982\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florencio_Campomanes\">Florencio Campomanes</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1982\n</td>\n<td>  1995\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kirsan_Ilyumzhinov\">Kirsan Ilyumzhinov</a>\n</td>\n<td>  1995\n</td>\n<td>  2018\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arkady_Dvorkovich\">Arkady Dvorkovich</a>\n</td>\n<td>  2018\n</td>\n<td>\n</td></tr></table>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"FIDE_and_ICGA\">FIDE and ICGA</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: FIDE and ICGA\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>The <a href=\"/ICGA\" title=\"ICGA\">ICGA</a> is recognized as Affiliated International Organization of the FIDE  <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>. \nThe <a href=\"/WCCC_2006\" title=\"WCCC 2006\">WCCC 2006</a> along with the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/37th_Chess_Olympiad\">37th Chess Olympiad</a> in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turin\">Turin</a> was the first and so far the only time the ICGA was “sequentially assembled” by the FIDE <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"FIDE_CC_Events\">FIDE CC Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: FIDE CC Events\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Deep_Fritz_versus_Deep_Junior_2007\" title=\"Deep Fritz versus Deep Junior 2007\">Deep Fritz versus Deep Junior 2007</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=14159\">Open Letter &amp; $100,000 challenge to FIDE</a> by <a href=\"/Vasik_Rajlich\" title=\"Vasik Rajlich\">Vasik Rajlich</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 31, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://rybkaforum.net/cgi-bin/rybkaforum/topic_show.pl?tid=25525\">Rybka &amp; ICGA at the FIDE Ethics Commission</a> by vesuvio, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Rybka Forum</a>, August 17, 2012&#160;» <a href=\"/Rybka_Controversy#FIDE\" title=\"Rybka Controversy\">Rybka Controversy | FIDE</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=59332\">a direct comparison of FIDE and CCRL rating systems</a> by <a href=\"/index.php?title=Erik_Varend&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Erik Varend (page does not exist)\">Erik Varend</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 22, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"/CCRL\" title=\"CCRL\">CCRL</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.fide.com/\">World Chess Federation - FIDE</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://handbook.fide.com/l\">FIDE Handbook</a></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://handbook.fide.com/chapter/E012018\">Laws of Chess</a></dd>\n<dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://handbook.fide.com/chapter/E03\">Regulations for Play with Computers</a></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE\">FIDE from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_Olympiad\">Chess Olympiad from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE_titles\">FIDE titles from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/fideprehistory.html\">FIDE: The Prehistory</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/fidehistory.html\">Chess: The History of FIDE</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/fidefacts.html\">The 1986 FIDE Presidential Election</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=FIDE&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIDE\">FIDE from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://main.uschess.org/content/view/8880/497/\">The United States Chess Federation - Larry Kaufman World Senior Champion!</a>, November 8, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Larry_Kaufman\" title=\"Larry Kaufman\">Larry Kaufman</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fidecongress2011.pl/en/fide\">FIDE - Recognized by the International Olympic Committee</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.fidecongress2011.pl/en\">82nd Fide Congress, 15-22 Oct 2011, Krakow</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1st_unofficial_Chess_Olympiad\">1st unofficial Chess Olympiad from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chesshistory.com/winter/extra/fidehistory.html\">Chess: The History of FIDE</a> by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Winter_%28chess_historian%29\">Edward Winter</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.fide.com/directory/affiliated-organizations\">Affiliated International Organizations</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Jaap_van_den_Herik\" title=\"Jaap van den Herik\">Jaap van den Herik</a> (<b>2008</b>). <i>Computer Games in China</i>. <a href=\"/ICGA_Journal#31_1\" title=\"ICGA Journal\">ICGA Journal, Vol. 31, No. 1</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/Organizations\" title=\"Organizations\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301024544\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.019 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.020 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 130/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 276/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls